df <- read.csv("GDIS_modify.csv", header=TRUE, sep=",", na.strings=" ")
df_mutate<-df %>%
  select(country,year,disastertype)
world_map<-map_data("world") %>%
  left_join(df_mutate,by=(c("region"="country")))
world_map %>%
  filter(year==2015) %>%
  group_by(disastertype,region)%>%
  mutate(count=n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=long,y=lat,group=group))+geom_polygon(aes(fill=count),color="white")+facet_wrap(vars(disastertype))

library(countrycode)
  world_map$continent <- countrycode(sourcevar = world_map[, "region"],
                            origin = "country.name",
                            destination = "continent")
## Warning in countrycode_convert(sourcevar = sourcevar, origin = origin, destination = dest, : Some values were not matched unambiguously: Antarctica, Ascension Island, Azores, Barbuda, Bonaire, Canary Islands, Chagos Archipelago, Cocos Islands, French Southern and Antarctic Lands, Grenadines, Heard Island, Kosovo, Madeira Islands, Micronesia, Saba, Saint Martin, Siachen Glacier, Sint Eustatius, South Georgia, South Sandwich Islands, Virgin Islands
world_map %>%
  filter(year==2015) %>%
  filter(continent!='') %>%
  group_by(continent,disastertype) %>%
  mutate(count=n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=long,y=lat,group=group))+geom_polygon(aes(fill=count),color="white")+facet_wrap(vars(continent),scales = "free")
